comment: @ryanh1129  Have you never heard of a compressor? It’s really easy to get even levels with high quality mics when you have high quality handheld mics and in ear monitoring. When they’re on headsets, their levels are indeed all over the place, but when they have handhelds, they’re able to control their levels. You can also hear when Minji is singing that she’s not 100% on pitch because you can hear her off the guide track a bit and you can hear her plosives popping. Meanwhile, Danielle is a stronger singer so she’s able to control levels better with better mic technique. It’s pretty easy to tell if you know how live sound works.
